t777.text: And now we have the commander in chief riling up local militias, using the loose 2nd amendment and mass proliferation of guns to control state governments. The 2nd has been turned on its head.

t778.text: Ergo, the city (I know, not a state, but the principle is the same) has a gun problem, which it is not allowed to control as it sees fit, and gives the feds a pretext for intervention in violation of state sovereignty.

t779.text: A few years ago Trump threatened to send the fed to Chicago to control the “carnage,” which Chicago had tried to control with handgun restrictions. The Supreme Court famously overturned those restrictions in McDonald v City of Chicago.

t780.text: Yes, 14a and all, but how does the imposition of 2a on states make sense? It was created for state militias. Unless, you wanted militias to use against the states. That may sound fine to some, but this creates opportunities for populists to use against local government.

t781.text: Again, the purpose of the 2nd was to allow state militias to resist the federal government. If arms within a state are not under their control, how can they form a bulwark against a tyrannical government? The terrible irony is it makes them vulnerable to federal intervention.

t782.text: Trump is invoking 2a as a threat of armed insurrection to control state governments.
